Unset Elimination Schemes.

Inductive token : Type :=
| XOR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| WHENOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| WHEN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| VAR_NAME : (Common.ident * LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| VAR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UNDERSCORE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT8 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT64 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT32 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| UINT16 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| TYPE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| THEN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| TEL : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| SWITCH : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| STAR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| SLASH : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| SEMICOLON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RRARROW : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RPAREN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RETURNS : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RESTART : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RESET : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| RARROW : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| PLUS : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| OR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ONOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| OF : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| NOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| NODE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| NEQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| MOD : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| MINUS : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| MERGE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LXOR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LSR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LSL : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LPAREN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LOR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LNOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LET : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LEQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LAST : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| LAND : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT8 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT64 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT32 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| INT16 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| IN : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| IFTE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| HASH : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| GT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| GEQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FUNCTION : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FLOAT64 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FLOAT32 : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| FBY : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| EXTERNAL : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| EVERY : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| EQ : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| EOF : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ENUM_NAME : (Common.ident * LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| END : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ELSE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| DOT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| DONE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| DO : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| CONSTANT : (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| COMMA : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| COLONCOLON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| COLON : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| CASE : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| BAR : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| ASSERT : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token
| AND : (LustreAst.astloc)%type -> token.

Definition terminal_semantic_type (t:terminal) : Type:=
  match t with
  | XOR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | WHENOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | WHEN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | VAR_NAME't => (Common.ident * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | VAR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UNDERSCORE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT8't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT64't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT32't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | UINT16't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | TYPE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | THEN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | TEL't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | SWITCH't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | STAR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | SLASH't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | SEMICOLON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RRARROW't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RPAREN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RETURNS't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RESTART't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RESET't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | RARROW't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | PLUS't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | OR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ONOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | OF't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | NOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | NODE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | NEQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | MOD't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | MINUS't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | MERGE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LXOR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LSR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LSL't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LPAREN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LOR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LNOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LET't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LEQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LAST't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | LAND't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT8't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT64't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT32't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | INT16't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | IN't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | IFTE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | HASH't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | GT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | GEQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FUNCTION't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FLOAT64't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FLOAT32't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | FBY't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | EXTERNAL't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | EVERY't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | EQ't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | EOF't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ENUM_NAME't => (Common.ident * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | END't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ELSE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | DOT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | DONE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | DO't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | CONSTANT't => (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | COMMA't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | COLONCOLON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | COLON't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | CASE't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | BAR't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | ASSERT't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | AND't => (LustreAst.astloc)%type
  end.

Definition nonterminal_semantic_type (nt:nonterminal) : Type:=
  match nt with
  | when_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | var_decl_list'nt => (LustreAst.local_decls)%type
  | var_decl'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls)%type
  | unary_operator'nt => (LustreAst.unary_operator * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | unary_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | type_names'nt => (list LustreAst.type_name)%type
  | type_name'nt => (LustreAst.type_name * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | translation_unit_file'nt => (list LustreAst.declaration)%type
  | translation_unit'nt => (list LustreAst.declaration)%type
  | switch_branch_list'nt => (list (Common.ident * list LustreAst.block))%type
  | shift_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | relational_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | primary_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | postfix_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | pattern'nt => (list Common.ident)%type
  | parameter_list'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls )%type
  | optsemicolon'nt => (unit)%type
  | optbar'nt => (unit)%type
  | oparameter_list'nt => (LustreAst.var_decls )%type
  | node_or_function'nt => (bool * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | multiplicative_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | logical_OR_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | logical_AND_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | local_decl_list'nt => (LustreAst.local_decls)%type
  | local_decl'nt => (LustreAst.local_decls)%type
  | last_var_decl'nt => (LustreAst.local_decls)%type
  | inclusive_OR_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | identifier_list'nt => (list Common.ident )%type
  | fby_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | expression_list'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | exclusive_OR_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | equation'nt => (LustreAst.equation)%type
  | equality_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | enum'nt => (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | declared_clock'nt => (LustreAst.preclock)%type
  | declaration'nt => (LustreAst.declaration)%type
  | constructor_list'nt => (list Common.ident)%type
  | constant'nt => (LustreAst.constant * LustreAst.astloc)%type
  | clock'nt => (LustreAst.clock)%type
  | cast_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | branch_list_with_default'nt => (list (Common.ident * list LustreAst.expression) * list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | branch_list'nt => (list (Common.ident * list LustreAst.expression))%type
  | blocks'nt => (list LustreAst.block)%type
  | block'nt => (LustreAst.block)%type
  | arrow_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | additive_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  | AND_expression'nt => (list LustreAst.expression)%type
  end.

Definition symbol_semantic_type (s:symbol) : Type:=
  match s with
  | T t => terminal_semantic_type t
  | NT nt => nonterminal_semantic_type nt
  end.

Definition token := token.

Definition token_term (tok : token) : terminal :=
  match tok with
  | XOR _ => XOR't
  | WHENOT _ => WHENOT't
  | WHEN _ => WHEN't
  | VAR_NAME _ => VAR_NAME't
  | VAR _ => VAR't
  | UNDERSCORE _ => UNDERSCORE't
  | UINT8 _ => UINT8't
  | UINT64 _ => UINT64't
  | UINT32 _ => UINT32't
  | UINT16 _ => UINT16't
  | TYPE _ => TYPE't
  | THEN _ => THEN't
  | TEL _ => TEL't
  | SWITCH _ => SWITCH't
  | STAR _ => STAR't
  | SLASH _ => SLASH't
  | SEMICOLON _ => SEMICOLON't
  | RRARROW _ => RRARROW't
  | RPAREN _ => RPAREN't
  | RETURNS _ => RETURNS't
  | RESTART _ => RESTART't
  | RESET _ => RESET't
  | RARROW _ => RARROW't
  | PLUS _ => PLUS't
  | OR _ => OR't
  | ONOT _ => ONOT't
  | ON _ => ON't
  | OF _ => OF't
  | NOT _ => NOT't
  | NODE _ => NODE't
  | NEQ _ => NEQ't
  | MOD _ => MOD't
  | MINUS _ => MINUS't
  | MERGE _ => MERGE't
  | LXOR _ => LXOR't
  | LT _ => LT't
  | LSR _ => LSR't
  | LSL _ => LSL't
  | LPAREN _ => LPAREN't
  | LOR _ => LOR't
  | LNOT _ => LNOT't
  | LET _ => LET't
  | LEQ _ => LEQ't
  | LAST _ => LAST't
  | LAND _ => LAND't
  | INT8 _ => INT8't
  | INT64 _ => INT64't
  | INT32 _ => INT32't
  | INT16 _ => INT16't
  | IN _ => IN't
  | IFTE _ => IFTE't
  | HASH _ => HASH't
  | GT _ => GT't
  | GEQ _ => GEQ't
  | FUNCTION _ => FUNCTION't
  | FLOAT64 _ => FLOAT64't
  | FLOAT32 _ => FLOAT32't
  | FBY _ => FBY't
  | EXTERNAL _ => EXTERNAL't
  | EVERY _ => EVERY't
  | EQ _ => EQ't
  | EOF _ => EOF't
  | ENUM_NAME _ => ENUM_NAME't
  | END _ => END't
  | ELSE _ => ELSE't
  | DOT _ => DOT't
  | DONE _ => DONE't
  | DO _ => DO't
  | CONSTANT _ => CONSTANT't
  | COMMA _ => COMMA't
  | COLONCOLON _ => COLONCOLON't
  | COLON _ => COLON't
  | CASE _ => CASE't
  | BAR _ => BAR't
  | ASSERT _ => ASSERT't
  | AND _ => AND't
  end.

    | 104%positive => Prod'declaration'0
    | 105%positive => Prod'constructor_list'1
    | 106%positive => Prod'constructor_list'0
    | 107%positive => Prod'constant'1
    | 108%positive => Prod'constant'0
    | 109%positive => Prod'clock'3
    | 110%positive => Prod'clock'2
    | 111%positive => Prod'clock'1
    | 112%positive => Prod'clock'0
    | 113%positive => Prod'cast_expression'1
    | 114%positive => Prod'cast_expression'0
    | 115%positive => Prod'branch_list_with_default'2
    | 116%positive => Prod'branch_list_with_default'1
    | 117%positive => Prod'branch_list_with_default'0
    | 118%positive => Prod'branch_list'1
    | 119%positive => Prod'branch_list'0
    | 120%positive => Prod'blocks'3
    | 121%positive => Prod'blocks'2
    | 122%positive => Prod'blocks'1
    | 123%positive => Prod'blocks'0
    | 124%positive => Prod'block'4
    | 125%positive => Prod'block'3
    | 126%positive => Prod'block'2
    | 127%positive => Prod'block'1
    | 128%positive => Prod'block'0
    | 129%positive => Prod'arrow_expression'1
    | 130%positive => Prod'arrow_expression'0
    | 131%positive => Prod'additive_expression'2
    | 132%positive => Prod'additive_expression'1
    | 133%positive => Prod'additive_expression'0
    | 134%positive => Prod'AND_expression'1
    | 135%positive => Prod'AND_expression'0
    | _ => Prod'when_expression'4
    end)%Z;
    inj_bound := 135%positive }.
Global Instance ProductionAlph : MenhirLib.Alphabet.Alphabet production := _.

Definition prod_contents (p:production) :
  { p:nonterminal * list symbol &
    MenhirLib.Grammar.arrows_right
      (symbol_semantic_type (NT (fst p)))
      (List.map symbol_semantic_type (snd p)) }
 :=
  let box := existT (fun p =>
    MenhirLib.Grammar.arrows_right
      (symbol_semantic_type (NT (fst p)))
      (List.map symbol_semantic_type (snd p)) )
  in
  match p with
  | Prod'AND_expression'0 => box
    (AND_expression'nt, [NT equality_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'AND_expression'1 => box
    (AND_expression'nt, [NT equality_expression'nt; T AND't; NT AND_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.BAND expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'additive_expression'0 => box
    (additive_expression'nt, [NT multiplicative_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'additive_expression'1 => box
    (additive_expression'nt, [NT multiplicative_expression'nt; T PLUS't; NT additive_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.ADD expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'additive_expression'2 => box
    (additive_expression'nt, [NT multiplicative_expression'nt; T MINUS't; NT additive_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.SUB expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'arrow_expression'0 => box
    (arrow_expression'nt, [NT logical_OR_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'arrow_expression'1 => box
    (arrow_expression'nt, [NT arrow_expression'nt; T RARROW't; NT logical_OR_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun e1 loc e0 =>
    ( [LustreAst.ARROW e0 e1 loc] )
)
  | Prod'block'0 => box
    (block'nt, [NT equation'nt]%list)
    (fun eq =>
   ( LustreAst.BEQ eq )
)
  | Prod'block'1 => box
    (block'nt, [NT expression'nt; T EVERY't; NT blocks'nt; T RESET't]%list)
    (fun er loc blks _1 =>
   ( LustreAst.BRESET blks er loc )
)
  | Prod'block'2 => box
    (block'nt, [T END't; NT switch_branch_list'nt; NT expression'nt; T SWITCH't]%list)
    (fun _4 brs ec loc =>
   ( LustreAst.BSWITCH ec brs loc )
)
  | Prod'block'3 => box
    (block'nt, [T DONE't; NT blocks'nt; T IN't; NT local_decl'nt; T DO't]%list)
    (fun _5 blks _3 locals loc =>
   ( LustreAst.BLOCAL locals blks loc )
)
  | Prod'block'4 => box
    (block'nt, [T TEL't; NT blocks'nt; T LET't; NT local_decl'nt]%list)
    (fun _4 blks loc locals =>
   ( LustreAst.BLOCAL locals blks loc )
)
  | Prod'blocks'0 => box
    (blocks'nt, []%list)
    (
    ( [] )
)
  | Prod'blocks'1 => box
    (blocks'nt, [NT block'nt]%list)
    (fun blk =>
    ( [blk] )
)
  | Prod'blocks'2 => box
    (blocks'nt, [NT blocks'nt; T SEMICOLON't; NT block'nt]%list)
    (fun blks _2 blk =>
    ( blk::blks )
)
  | Prod'blocks'3 => box
    (blocks'nt, [NT blocks'nt; T SEMICOLON't; NT expression'nt; T ASSERT't]%list)
    (fun blks _3 _2 _1 =>
    ( blks )
)
  | Prod'branch_list'0 => box
    (branch_list'nt, [T RPAREN't; NT expression'nt; T RRARROW't; T ENUM_NAME't; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun _5 expr _3 c _1 =>
    ( [(fst c, expr)] )
)
  | Prod'branch_list'1 => box
    (branch_list'nt, [NT branch_list'nt; T RPAREN't; NT expression'nt; T RRARROW't; T ENUM_NAME't; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun bs _5 expr _3 c _1 =>
    ( (fst c, expr) :: bs )
)
  | Prod'branch_list_with_default'0 => box
    (branch_list_with_default'nt, [T RPAREN't; NT expression'nt; T RRARROW't; T UNDERSCORE't; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun _5 expr _3 _2 _1 =>
    ( [], expr )
)
  | Prod'branch_list_with_default'1 => box
    (branch_list_with_default'nt, [T RPAREN't; NT expression'nt; T RRARROW't; T ENUM_NAME't; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun _5 expr _3 c _1 =>
    ( [(fst c, expr)], [] )
)
  | Prod'branch_list_with_default'2 => box
    (branch_list_with_default'nt, [NT branch_list_with_default'nt; T RPAREN't; NT expression'nt; T RRARROW't; T ENUM_NAME't; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun bs _5 expr _3 c _1 =>
    ( (fst c, expr) :: (fst bs), (snd bs) )
)
  | Prod'cast_expression'0 => box
    (cast_expression'nt, [NT unary_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'cast_expression'1 => box
    (cast_expression'nt, [T RPAREN't; NT type_name'nt; T COLON't; NT cast_expression'nt; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun _5 typ loc expr _1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.CAST (fst typ) expr loc] )
)
  | Prod'clock'0 => box
    (clock'nt, [T DOT't]%list)
    (fun _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.BASE )
)
  | Prod'clock'1 => box
    (clock'nt, [T RPAREN't; T VAR_NAME't; T LPAREN't; T ENUM_NAME't; T ON't; NT clock'nt]%list)
    (fun _6 id _4 c _2 clk =>
    ( LustreAst.ON clk (fst id) (fst c) )
)
  | Prod'clock'2 => box
    (clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T ON't; NT clock'nt]%list)
    (fun id _2 clk =>
    ( LustreAst.ON clk (fst id) true_id )
)
  | Prod'clock'3 => box
    (clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T ONOT't; NT clock'nt]%list)
    (fun id _2 clk =>
    ( LustreAst.ON clk (fst id) false_id )
)
  | Prod'constant'0 => box
    (constant'nt, [T CONSTANT't]%list)
    (fun cst =>
    ( cst )
)
  | Prod'constant'1 => box
    (constant'nt, [NT enum'nt]%list)
    (fun c =>
    ( c )
)
  | Prod'constructor_list'0 => box
    (constructor_list'nt, [T ENUM_NAME't]%list)
    (fun id =>
    ( [fst id] )
)
  | Prod'constructor_list'1 => box
    (constructor_list'nt, [NT constructor_list'nt; T BAR't; T ENUM_NAME't]%list)
    (fun idl _2 id =>
    ( fst id :: idl )
)
  | Prod'declaration'0 => box
    (declaration'nt, [NT optsemicolon'nt; T TEL't; NT blocks'nt; T LET't; NT local_decl_list'nt; NT optsemicolon'nt; T RPAREN't; NT oparameter_list'nt; T LPAREN't; T RETURNS't; NT optsemicolon'nt; T RPAREN't; NT oparameter_list'nt; T LPAREN't; T VAR_NAME't; NT node_or_function'nt]%list)
    (fun _16 _15 blks loc locals _11 _10 oparams _8 _7 _6 _5 iparams _3 id is_node =>
    ( LustreAst.NODE
        (fst id) (fst is_node) iparams oparams (LustreAst.BLOCAL locals blks loc) (snd is_node) )
)
  | Prod'declaration'1 => box
    (declaration'nt, [NT constructor_list'nt; NT optbar'nt; T EQ't; T VAR_NAME't; T TYPE't]%list)
    (fun cs _4 _3 id loc =>
    ( LustreAst.TYPE (fst id) cs loc )
)
  | Prod'declaration'2 => box
    (declaration'nt, [NT type_name'nt; T RETURNS't; T RPAREN't; NT type_names'nt; T LPAREN't; T VAR_NAME't; T EXTERNAL't]%list)
    (fun tyout _6 _5 tyins _3 id loc =>
    ( LustreAst.EXTERNAL (fst id) tyins (fst tyout) loc )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'0 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, []%list)
    (
    ( LustreAst.FULLCK LustreAst.BASE )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'1 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [T RPAREN't; T VAR_NAME't; T LPAREN't; T ENUM_NAME't; T WHEN't]%list)
    (fun _5 id _3 c _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.WHENCK (fst id) (fst c) )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'2 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T WHEN't]%list)
    (fun id _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.WHENCK (fst id) true_id )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'3 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T NOT't; T WHEN't]%list)
    (fun id _2 _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.WHENCK (fst id) false_id )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'4 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T WHENOT't]%list)
    (fun id _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.WHENCK (fst id) false_id )
)
  | Prod'declared_clock'5 => box
    (declared_clock'nt, [NT clock'nt; T COLONCOLON't]%list)
    (fun clk _1 =>
    ( LustreAst.FULLCK clk )
)
  | Prod'enum'0 => box
    (enum'nt, [T ENUM_NAME't]%list)
    (fun c =>
    ( (LustreAst.CONST_ENUM (fst c), snd c) )
)
  | Prod'equality_expression'0 => box
    (equality_expression'nt, [NT relational_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'equality_expression'1 => box
    (equality_expression'nt, [NT relational_expression'nt; T EQ't; NT equality_expression'nt]%list)

    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.EQ expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'equality_expression'2 => box
    (equality_expression'nt, [NT relational_expression'nt; T NEQ't; NT equality_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.NE expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'equation'0 => box
    (equation'nt, [NT expression'nt; T EQ't; NT pattern'nt]%list)
    (fun exp loc pat =>
    ( (rev pat, exp, loc) )
)
  | Prod'equation'1 => box
    (equation'nt, [NT expression'nt; T EQ't; T RPAREN't; NT pattern'nt; T LPAREN't]%list)
    (fun exp loc _3 pat _1 =>
    ( (rev pat, exp, loc) )
)
  | Prod'exclusive_OR_expression'0 => box
    (exclusive_OR_expression'nt, [NT AND_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'exclusive_OR_expression'1 => box
    (exclusive_OR_expression'nt, [NT AND_expression'nt; T LXOR't; NT exclusive_OR_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.XOR expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'exclusive_OR_expression'2 => box
    (exclusive_OR_expression'nt, [NT AND_expression'nt; T XOR't; NT exclusive_OR_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.XOR expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'expression'0 => box
    (expression'nt, [NT arrow_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'expression'1 => box
    (expression'nt, [NT expression'nt; T ELSE't; NT expression'nt; T THEN't; NT expression'nt; T IFTE't]%list)
    (fun expr3 _5 expr2 _3 expr1 loc =>
    ( [LustreAst.CASE expr1 [(true_id, expr2); (false_id, expr3)] [] loc] )
)
  | Prod'expression'2 => box
    (expression'nt, [NT branch_list_with_default'nt; T OF't; NT expression'nt; T CASE't]%list)
    (fun brs _3 expr loc =>
    ( [LustreAst.CASE expr (fst brs) (snd brs) loc] )
)
  | Prod'expression'3 => box
    (expression'nt, [NT primary_expression'nt; NT primary_expression'nt; T VAR_NAME't; T MERGE't]%list)
    (fun expr2 expr1 id loc =>
    ( [LustreAst.MERGE (fst id) [(true_id, expr1); (false_id, expr2)] loc] )
)
  | Prod'expression'4 => box
    (expression'nt, [NT branch_list'nt; T VAR_NAME't; T MERGE't]%list)
    (fun bs id loc =>
    ( [LustreAst.MERGE (fst id) bs loc] )
)
  | Prod'expression_list'0 => box
    (expression_list'nt, [NT expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'expression_list'1 => box
    (expression_list'nt, [NT expression'nt; T COMMA't; NT expression_list'nt]%list)
    (fun expr _2 exprs =>
    ( expr ++ exprs )
)
  | Prod'fby_expression'0 => box
    (fby_expression'nt, [NT cast_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'fby_expression'1 => box
    (fby_expression'nt, [NT fby_expression'nt; T FBY't; NT cast_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr loc v0 =>
    ( [LustreAst.FBY v0 expr loc] )
)
  | Prod'identifier_list'0 => box
    (identifier_list'nt, [T VAR_NAME't]%list)

    ( [fst id] )
)
  | Prod'identifier_list'1 => box
    (identifier_list'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T COMMA't; NT identifier_list'nt]%list)

  | Prod'inclusive_OR_expression'0 => box

    ( expr )

    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.BOR expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'last_var_decl'0 => box

    ( vars_list )

    ( [] )

    ( [] )

    ( vars_list )

    ( () )

    ( () )

    ( () )

  | Prod'relational_expression'0 => box
    (relational_expression'nt, [NT when_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'relational_expression'1 => box
    (relational_expression'nt, [NT when_expression'nt; T LT't; NT relational_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.LT expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'relational_expression'2 => box
    (relational_expression'nt, [NT when_expression'nt; T GT't; NT relational_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.GT expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'relational_expression'3 => box
    (relational_expression'nt, [NT when_expression'nt; T LEQ't; NT relational_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.LE expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'relational_expression'4 => box
    (relational_expression'nt, [NT when_expression'nt; T GEQ't; NT relational_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.GE expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'shift_expression'0 => box
    (shift_expression'nt, [NT additive_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'shift_expression'1 => box
    (shift_expression'nt, [NT additive_expression'nt; T LSL't; NT shift_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.LSL expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'shift_expression'2 => box
    (shift_expression'nt, [NT additive_expression'nt; T LSR't; NT shift_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr2 loc expr1 =>
    ( [LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.LSR expr1 expr2 loc] )
)
  | Prod'switch_branch_list'0 => box
    (switch_branch_list'nt, [NT blocks'nt; T DO't; T ENUM_NAME't; T BAR't]%list)
    (fun blk _3 c _1 =>
    ( [(fst c, blk)] )
)
  | Prod'switch_branch_list'1 => box
    (switch_branch_list'nt, [NT switch_branch_list'nt; NT blocks'nt; T DO't; T ENUM_NAME't; T BAR't]%list)
    (fun bs blk _3 c _1 =>
    ( (fst c, blk) :: bs )
)
  | Prod'translation_unit'0 => box
    (translation_unit'nt, [NT declaration'nt]%list)
    (fun def =>
    ( [def] )
)
  | Prod'translation_unit'1 => box
    (translation_unit'nt, [NT declaration'nt; NT translation_unit'nt]%list)
    (fun deft defq =>
    ( deft::defq )
)
  | Prod'translation_unit_file'0 => box
    (translation_unit_file'nt, [T EOF't; NT translation_unit'nt]%list)
    (fun _2 lst =>
    ( List.rev lst )
)
  | Prod'translation_unit_file'1 => box
    (translation_unit_file'nt, [T EOF't]%list)
    (fun _1 =>
    ( [] )
)
  | Prod'type_name'0 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T INT8't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tint8, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'1 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T UINT8't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tuint8, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'2 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T INT16't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tint16, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'3 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T UINT16't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tuint16, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'4 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T INT32't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tint32, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'5 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T UINT32't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tuint32, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'6 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T INT64't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tint64, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'7 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T UINT64't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tuint64, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'8 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T FLOAT32't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tfloat32, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'9 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T FLOAT64't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tfloat64, loc) )
)
  | Prod'type_name'10 => box
    (type_name'nt, [T VAR_NAME't]%list)
    (fun t =>
    ( (LustreAst.Tenum_name (fst t), snd t) )
)
  | Prod'type_names'0 => box
    (type_names'nt, [NT type_name'nt]%list)
    (fun typ =>
                ( [fst typ] )
)
  | Prod'type_names'1 => box
    (type_names'nt, [NT type_names'nt; T COMMA't; NT type_name'nt]%list)
    (fun tys _2 ty =>
                                    ( (fst ty)::tys )
)
  | Prod'unary_expression'0 => box
    (unary_expression'nt, [NT postfix_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'unary_expression'1 => box
    (unary_expression'nt, [NT cast_expression'nt; NT unary_operator'nt]%list)
    (fun expr op =>
    ( [LustreAst.UNARY (fst op) expr (snd op)] )
)
  | Prod'unary_expression'2 => box
    (unary_expression'nt, [T RPAREN't; NT expression_list'nt; T LPAREN't; T HASH't]%list)
    (fun _4 args _2 loc =>
    (
       [LustreAst.BINARY
         LustreAst.LE
         [fold_right (fun es e => LustreAst.BINARY LustreAst.ADD [e] [es] loc)
         (LustreAst.CONSTANT (LustreAst.CONST_INT LustreAst.string_zero) loc)
         (map (fun e =>
                LustreAst.CASE [e]
                 [(Ident.Ids.true_id, [LustreAst.CONSTANT (LustreAst.CONST_INT LustreAst.string_one) loc]);
                  (Ident.Ids.false_id, [LustreAst.CONSTANT (LustreAst.CONST_INT LustreAst.string_zero) loc])] [] loc)
              args)]
      [LustreAst.CONSTANT (LustreAst.CONST_INT LustreAst.string_one) loc]
     loc]
     )
)
  | Prod'unary_operator'0 => box
    (unary_operator'nt, [T MINUS't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.MINUS, loc) )
)
  | Prod'unary_operator'1 => box
    (unary_operator'nt, [T LNOT't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.NOT, loc) )
)
  | Prod'unary_operator'2 => box
    (unary_operator'nt, [T NOT't]%list)
    (fun loc =>
    ( (LustreAst.BNOT, loc) )
)
  | Prod'var_decl'0 => box
    (var_decl'nt, [NT declared_clock'nt; NT type_name'nt; T COLON't; NT identifier_list'nt]%list)
    (fun clk ty loc ids =>
    ( map (fun id => (id, (fst ty, clk, loc))) (rev ids) )
)
  | Prod'var_decl_list'0 => box
    (var_decl_list'nt, [T SEMICOLON't; NT last_var_decl'nt]%list)
    (fun _2 vars =>
    ( vars )
)
  | Prod'var_decl_list'1 => box
    (var_decl_list'nt, [NT var_decl_list'nt; T SEMICOLON't; NT last_var_decl'nt]%list)
    (fun vars_list _2 vars =>
    ( vars ++ vars_list )
)
  | Prod'when_expression'0 => box
    (when_expression'nt, [NT shift_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun expr =>
    ( expr )
)
  | Prod'when_expression'1 => box
    (when_expression'nt, [T RPAREN't; T VAR_NAME't; T LPAREN't; T ENUM_NAME't; T WHEN't; NT when_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun _6 id _4 c loc expr =>
    ( [LustreAst.WHEN expr (fst id) (fst c) loc] )
)
  | Prod'when_expression'2 => box
    (when_expression'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T WHEN't; NT when_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun id loc expr =>
    ( [LustreAst.WHEN expr (fst id) true_id loc] )
)
  | Prod'when_expression'3 => box
    (when_expression'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T NOT't; T WHEN't; NT when_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun id _3 loc expr =>
    ( [LustreAst.WHEN expr (fst id) false_id loc] )
)
  | Prod'when_expression'4 => box
    (when_expression'nt, [T VAR_NAME't; T WHENOT't; NT when_expression'nt]%list)
    (fun id loc expr =>
    ( [LustreAst.WHEN expr (fst id) false_id loc] )
)
  end.

Definition prod_lhs (p:production) :=
  fst (projT1 (prod_contents p)).
Definition prod_rhs_rev (p:production) :=
  snd (projT1 (prod_contents p)).
Definition prod_action (p:production) :=
  projT2 (prod_contents p).

End Gram.

Definition nullable_nterm (nt:nonterminal) : bool :=
  match nt with
  | when_expression'nt => false
  | var_decl_list'nt => false
  | var_decl'nt => false
  | unary_operator'nt => false
  | unary_expression'nt => false
  | type_names'nt => false
  | type_name'nt => false
  | translation_unit_file'nt => false
  | translation_unit'nt => false
  | switch_branch_list'nt => false
  | shift_expression'nt => false
  | relational_expression'nt => false
  | primary_expression'nt => false
  | postfix_expression'nt => false
  | pattern'nt => false
  | parameter_list'nt => false
  | optsemicolon'nt => true
  | optbar'nt => true
  | oparameter_list'nt => true
  | node_or_function'nt => false
  | multiplicative_expression'nt => false
  | logical_OR_expression'nt => false
  | logical_AND_expression'nt => false
  | local_decl_list'nt => true
  | local_decl'nt => false
  | last_var_decl'nt => false
  | inclusive_OR_expression'nt => false
  | identifier_list'nt => false
  | fby_expression'nt => false
  | expression_list'nt => false
  | expression'nt => false
  | exclusive_OR_expression'nt => false
  | equation'nt => false
  | equality_expression'nt => false
  | enum'nt => false
  | declared_clock'nt => true
  | declaration'nt => false
  | constructor_list'nt => false
  | constant'nt => false
  | clock'nt => false
  | cast_expression'nt => false
  | branch_list_with_default'nt => false
  | branch_list'nt => false
  | blocks'nt => true
  | block'nt => false
  | arrow_expression'nt => false
  | additive_expression'nt => false
  | AND_expression'nt => false
  end.

Definition first_nterm (nt:nonterminal) : list terminal :=
  match nt with
  | when_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | var_decl_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't; LAST't]%list
  | var_decl'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | unary_operator'nt => [NOT't; MINUS't; LNOT't]%list
  | unary_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | type_names'nt => [VAR_NAME't; UINT8't; UINT64't; UINT32't; UINT16't; INT8't; INT64't; INT32't; INT16't; FLOAT64't; FLOAT32't]%list
  | type_name'nt => [VAR_NAME't; UINT8't; UINT64't; UINT32't; UINT16't; INT8't; INT64't; INT32't; INT16't; FLOAT64't; FLOAT32't]%list
  | translation_unit_file'nt => [TYPE't; NODE't; FUNCTION't; EXTERNAL't; EOF't]%list
  | translation_unit'nt => [TYPE't; NODE't; FUNCTION't; EXTERNAL't]%list
  | switch_branch_list'nt => [BAR't]%list
  | shift_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | relational_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | primary_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; LPAREN't; LAST't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | postfix_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; LPAREN't; LAST't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | pattern'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | parameter_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | optsemicolon'nt => [SEMICOLON't]%list
  | optbar'nt => [BAR't]%list
  | oparameter_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | node_or_function'nt => [NODE't; FUNCTION't]%list
  | multiplicative_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | logical_OR_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | logical_AND_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | local_decl_list'nt => [VAR't]%list
  | local_decl'nt => [VAR't]%list
  | last_var_decl'nt => [VAR_NAME't; LAST't]%list
  | inclusive_OR_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | identifier_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't]%list
  | fby_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | expression_list'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; MERGE't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; IFTE't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't; CASE't]%list
  | expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; MERGE't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; IFTE't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't; CASE't]%list
  | exclusive_OR_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | equation'nt => [VAR_NAME't; LPAREN't]%list
  | equality_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | enum'nt => [ENUM_NAME't]%list
  | declared_clock'nt => [WHENOT't; WHEN't; COLONCOLON't]%list
  | declaration'nt => [TYPE't; NODE't; FUNCTION't; EXTERNAL't]%list
  | constructor_list'nt => [ENUM_NAME't]%list
  | constant'nt => [ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | clock'nt => [DOT't]%list
  | cast_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | branch_list_with_default'nt => [LPAREN't]%list
  | branch_list'nt => [LPAREN't]%list
  | blocks'nt => [VAR_NAME't; VAR't; SWITCH't; RESET't; LPAREN't; DO't; ASSERT't]%list
  | block'nt => [VAR_NAME't; VAR't; SWITCH't; RESET't; LPAREN't; DO't]%list
  | arrow_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | additive_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  | AND_expression'nt => [VAR_NAME't; NOT't; MINUS't; LPAREN't; LNOT't; LAST't; HASH't; ENUM_NAME't; CONSTANT't]%list
  end.

Inductive initstate' : Set :=
| Init'0.
Definition initstate := initstate'.

Global Program Instance initstateNum : MenhirLib.Alphabet.Numbered initstate :=
  { inj := fun x => match x return _ with
    | Init'0 => 1%positive
    end;
    surj := (fun n => match n return _ with
    | 1%positive => Init'0
    | _ => Init'0
    end)%Z;
    inj_bound := 1%positive }.
Global Instance InitStateAlph : MenhirLib.Alphabet.Alphabet initstate := _.

Include MenhirLib.Automaton.Types.

Definition start_nt (init:initstate) : nonterminal :=
  match init with
  | Init'0 => translation_unit_file'nt
  end.

Definition action_table (state:state) : action :=
  match state with
  | Init Init'0 => Lookahead_act (fun terminal:terminal =>
    match terminal return lookahead_action terminal with
    | TYPE't => Shift_act Nis'1 (eq_refl _)
    | NODE't => Shift_act Nis'10 (eq_refl _)
    | FUNCTION't => Shift_act Nis'11 (eq_refl _)
    | EXTERNAL't => Shift_act Nis'12 (eq_refl _)
    | EOF't => Shift_act Nis'33 (eq_refl _)
    | _ => Fail_act
    end)
  | Ninit Nis'1 => Lookahead_act (fun terminal:terminal =>
    match terminal return lookahead_action terminal with
    | VAR_NAME't => Shift_act Nis'2 (eq_refl _)
    | _ => Fail_act
    end)
  | Ninit Nis'2 => Lookahead_act (fun terminal:terminal =>
    match terminal return lookahead_action terminal with
    | EQ't => Shift_act Nis'3 (eq_refl _)
    | _ => Fail_act
    end)
  | Ninit Nis'3 => Lookahead_act (fun terminal:terminal =>
    match terminal return lookahead_action terminal with
    | ENUM_NAME't => Reduce_act Prod'optbar'0
    | BAR't => Shift_act Nis'4 (eq_refl _)
    | _ => Fail_act
    end)
  | Ninit Nis'4 => Default_reduce_act Prod'optbar'1
  | Ninit Nis'5 => Lookahead_act (fun terminal:terminal =>

    match terminal return lookahead_action terminal with
    | TYPE't => Reduce_act Prod'constructor_list'0
    | NODE't => Reduce_act Prod'constructor_list'0
    | FUNCTION't => Reduce_act Prod'constructor_list'0
    | EXTERNAL't => Reduce_act Prod'constructor_list'0
    | EOF't => Reduce_act Prod'constructor_list'0
    | BAR't => Shift_act Nis'7 (eq_refl _)
    | _ => Fail_act
    end)

Module MenhirLibParser := MenhirLib.Main.Make Aut.
Theorem safe:
  MenhirLibParser.safe_validator tt = true.
Proof eq_refl true<:MenhirLibParser.safe_validator tt = true.

Theorem complete:
  MenhirLibParser.complete_validator tt = true.
Proof eq_refl true<:MenhirLibParser.complete_validator tt = true.

Definition translation_unit_file : nat -> MenhirLibParser.Inter.buffer -> MenhirLibParser.Inter.parse_result (list LustreAst.declaration) := MenhirLibParser.parse safe Aut.Init'0.

Theorem translation_unit_file_correct (log_fuel : nat) (buffer : MenhirLibParser.Inter.buffer):
  match translation_unit_file log_fuel buffer with
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Parsed_pr sem buffer_new =>
      exists word (tree : Gram.parse_tree (NT translation_unit_file'nt) word),
        buffer = MenhirLibParser.Inter.app_buf word buffer_new /\
        Gram.pt_sem tree = sem
  | _ => True
  end.
Proof.
apply MenhirLibParser.parse_correct with (init:=Aut.Init'0). Qed.

Theorem translation_unit_file_complete (log_fuel : nat) (word : list token) (buffer_end : MenhirLibParser.Inter.buffer) :
  forall tree : Gram.parse_tree (NT translation_unit_file'nt) word,
  match translation_unit_file log_fuel (MenhirLibParser.Inter.app_buf word buffer_end) with
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Fail_pr => False
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Parsed_pr output_res buffer_end_res =>
      output_res = Gram.pt_sem tree /\
      buffer_end_res = buffer_end /\ (Gram.pt_size tree <= PeanoNat.Nat.pow 2 log_fuel)%nat
  | MenhirLibParser.Inter.Timeout_pr => (PeanoNat.Nat.pow 2 log_fuel < Gram.pt_size tree)%nat
  end.
Proof.
apply MenhirLibParser.parse_complete with (init:=Aut.Init'0); exact complete. Qed.
